{"key":"processedPost-20052981","value":{"id":20052981,"first":20052387,"last":20052981,"when":1401326729,"utime":"05/29/14 04:25 AM","cleanedPost":"WBS has smaller kernels than rye berries so you have to be careful of overhydration.&nbsp; It doesn't matter how long you let grains 'drain', water only drips for the first minute or so.&nbsp; The rest sticks by adhesion to the grains where it may or may not make the batch too wet.<br />On your first time with WBS, just try to make sure the grains are damp but not wet before loading the jars.&nbsp; Slightly too dry is always better than too wet.<br />RR"}}